Part I - San Francisco Ford Go Bike Dataset Exploration.¶

by Otim William Gerison¶

Introduction¶

This dataset includes information about individual rides made in a bike-sharing system covering the greater San Francisco Bay area.

The features in the dataset include the following:

duration_sec
start_time
end_time
start_station_id
start_station_name
start_station_latitude
start_station_longitude end_station_id
end_station_name
end_station_latitude
end_station_longitude
bike_id
user_type member_birth_year member_gender bike_share_for_all_trip

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

From the dataset, the fatures of primary interest include start_time, end_time, duration_sec, user_type featues.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

I think the features that will help our investigation most are start / end time and user type.

# Creating a function to handle labelling properties like xlabel, ylabel and title.
def properties_label(title, xlab, ylab):
    plt.title(title)
    plt.xlabel(xlab)
    plt.ylabel(ylab)

Talk about some of the relationships you observed in this part of the investigation. How did the feature(s) of interest vary with other features in the dataset?¶

There is a of correlation between duration and user type in regard to the fact that Subscribers tends to have a shorter usage time than Customers.

Did you observe any interesting relationships between the other features (not the main feature(s) of interest)?¶

Subscriber usage time is peak between 8 and 9 as well as 5 and 6 contrary to Customers with a more flexible usage time.

Talk about some of the relationships you observed in this part of the investigation. Were there features that strengthened each other in terms of looking at your feature(s) of interest?¶

Subcribers have a more set usage period while Customers have a flexible time for riding.

Were there any interesting or surprising interactions between features?¶

It is surprising that customers have a peak usage time at 3: 00 am.

Conclusions¶

The dataset is for only February.

Customers have a higher duration than subscribers.

The average duration for all trips is about 500 seconds.

The rush hours of going to work that is between 8 and 9 in the morning and going home in the evening that is between 5 and 6 have the highest trip taken.

Most trips were taken on Thursdays and Tuesdays while the least were over weekends.

Females spend more duration on rides than males.

Only subscribers are allowed to share bikes on trips.
